message.content:
1. Was the Calendar (New Style) Act 1750 (c. 23) indeed an act of the Parliament of Great Britain?
2. Can you provide specific details on how the act reformed the calendar of England and the British dominions with regards to the start of the new legal year?
3. Why is the act sometimes referred to as Chesterfield's Act and how is Philip Stanhope, 4th Earl of Chesterfield, connected to it?
4. When did the Calendar (New Style) Act 1750 come into effect, and how did it impact the transition from the old calendar system to the new one?
